node.text: When it's too hot out to turn on your oven, the time is right to experience the phenomenal crisp texture and flavor of grilled pizza. Happy Pride Month! Watch how the King Arthur Baking community is kicking off celebrations. ❤️🧡💛💚💙💜

"We celebrate Pride because we are committed to a more diverse and inclusive future — and we want to show up for each other." - Karen Colberg, King Arthur Baking co-CEO

King Arthur Baking Company is making a donation to @TheTrevorProject, which provides crisis intervention and suicide prevention services to lesbian, gay, bisexual, transgender, queer & questioning (LGBTQ) young people under 25. We encourage you to learn more and donate at bakewith.us/TrevorProject

node.title: Celebrate Pride With Us - King Arthur Baking Company - Pride 2021

node.text: Think cinnamon rolls are out of your baking wheelhouse? Think again! Our own Kye @life.of.kye is here to take you step-by-step through our #recipeoftheyear, Perfectly Pillowy Cinnamon Rolls. With a friend by your virtual side, you’re destined for cinnamon-swirled success! Share your rolls with #recipeoftheyear and #KingArthurBaking

node.title: Bake it Better with Kye: How to make Perfectly Pillowy Cinnamon Rolls

node.accessibility_caption: A baker pours dough into a bowl. Photo by King Arthur Baking.

node.text: Not being the easiest project to dive into without a guide, our own PJ is here with her best tips on all things sourdough baking. This blog has been helping out sourdough bakers for years — you're in good hands! Check out her tips at the link in our profile >> @kingarthurbaking, and share your next sourdough bake with #KingArthurBaking

node.accessibility_caption: A slice of decadent bumpy cake on a plate. Photo by King Arthur Baking.

node.text: Your fork is in for a bumpy ride — and a tasty one at that! Coated in a thick sheet of rich fudge frosting, “Bumpy Cake” is a Detroit classic. Stripes of vanilla buttercream hide beneath the fudge to create delicious “bumps” in every bite. Find the recipe at the link in our profile >> @kingarthurbaking, and share your bumpy cake with #KingArthurBaking

node.accessibility_caption: An overhead view of a table set with burger fixings, including homemade buns, lettuce, tomato, pickle, onion, and condiments. Photo by King Arthur Baking.

node.text: Labor Day weekend wouldn’t be the same without a little backyard grilling. Take your cookout up a notch with the highest-rated recipe on our website: Beautiful Burger Buns! Soft, golden, and the favorite of over 1200 5-star reviewers, they’re the perfect vessel for your burgers — meat or plant-based — this weekend. Find the recipe linked in our profile >> @kingarthurbaking, and share your burger buns with #KingArthurBaking. Happy grilling!

node.accessibility_caption: A top down shot of a container of hungry starter, a small bowl of flour, and a rubber spatula. -Photo shared by King Arthur Baking

node.text: Gray, grimy, and smelling of nail polish remover … not exactly the starter you want to make sourdough bread from! But all it needs is a little TLC. Our resident “Casual Sourdough Baker” PJ knows that when you don’t feel like baking sourdough, it’s totally fine to park it in the fridge until you’re ready. Tap the link in our profile >> @kingarthurbaking to see how you can let your starter hibernate without killing it. Share your sourdough bakes with #KingArthurBaking.

node.accessibility_caption: A top down shot of a cheesecake with a swirled filling throughout on a round serving plate, with four slices of the cake cut and one slice on a small round plate. -Photo shared by King Arthur Baking

node.text: If you bake one thing this weekend, make it this Halvah Cheesecake courtesy of @ZingermansBakehouse! Rich and indulgent without being overly sweet, this Rosh Hashanah favorite is dotted with sesame halvah and swirled with chocolate and vanilla tahini. Did we mention it has a brownie crust? Did we even need to because you’re already pulling out the ingredients to start baking? That’s what we thought! Find the recipe at the link in our profile >> @kingarthurbaking, and share your Halvah Cheesecake with #KingArthurBaking

node.accessibility_caption: A sliced up loaf of Cinnamon Apple Twist bread. Photo by King Arthur Baking.

node.text: Whether sliced up for breakfast or savored during dessert, Cinnamon-Apple Twist Bread is a little loaf of comfort. With soft dough and spiced apple filling, a drizzle of vanilla glaze adds the perfect touch of sweetness. Find the recipe at the link in our profile >> @kingarthurbaking, and share how you’re baking with apples with #KingArthurBaking

node.accessibility_caption: Sliced bread, meat, and olives on a board. Photo by King Arthur Baking.

node.text: When you realize you forgot to add yeast or salt to bread dough after it’s already rising (or sitting like a lump if you left out the yeast), you may feel a wave of bread dread. Instead of throwing in the towel, head over to our blog where our own @banannabelles tapped into the brilliant minds from our Baker’s Hotline to find out just how to fix it. Click the link in our profile >> @kingarthurbaking to see how, and share your finished loaf with #KingArthurBaking

node.accessibility_caption: Fresh corn tortillas with all the fixings, perfect for taco night. Photo by King Arthur Baking.

node.text: Made from 100% American-grown Certified Organic white corn, our finely ground masa harina is easy to work with and can be used in any number of recipes. From traditional tortillas and tamales to fun twists like Whipped Lemon Shortbread and Sweet Corn Cookies, our Masa Harina recipe collection will have your table filled with tasty dishes from dawn to dusk. Check it out at the link in our profile >> @kingarthurbaking, and share your masa harina bakes with #KingArthurBaking

node.accessibility_caption: Baking Ambassador Martin Phillip smells a loaf of bread. Photo by King Arthur Baking.

node.text: Martin @breadwright is here to put you on the road to perfectly chewy, crispy bread. How? With his 5 best tips for working with high-hydrations doughs! Check it out at the link in our profile >> @kingarthurbaking, and share your next loaf with #KingArthurBaking

node.accessibility_caption: A top down shot of cookies on a piece of parchment paper, next to a glass of milk. -Photo shared by King Arthur Baking

node.text: Roughly 7 billion chocolate chip cookies are eaten every year, but if more people tried brown butter chocolate chip cookies, that number would easily double. @joythebaker’s simple trick for browning half the butter in her dough creates an irresistible nutty flavor. Check out this butter trick for better chocolate chip cookies and bake her recipe by tapping the link in our profile >> @kingarthurbaking. Share your batch with #KingArthurBaking

node.accessibility_caption: A top down shot of cookies on a round cooling rack with more on a small serving plate and some waiting to be coated in confectioners’ sugar. -Photo shared by King Arthur Baking

node.text:
We're pleased to introduce the final 2021 feature of Baking a Stand, an initiative created to counter racial injustice in the food system. Mariela Camacho, of @comadre_panaderia, has generously shared the recipe for her special cookie, Horchata Polvoron, with the King Arthur Bakery and website. Reminiscent of a wedding cookie, you don't want to miss this spiced treat. Mariela’s mission is rooted in social and environmental stewardship and mentorship of women and people of color.

This cookie will be sold in our Norwich, Vermont café from now into the fall, and all proceeds will be donated to the @VTReleafCollective. Learn more and support this BIPOC network of Vermonters passionate about the environment, agriculture, and equitable foodways at the link in our profile >> @kingarthurbaking. Bake Mariella’s recipe (also linked) and share your batch with #KingArthurBaking

node.text:
The amazing folks from @miriamskitchen and @dogtagbakery in Washington D.C. recently partnered together through our For Goodness Bakes program with the shared mission of feeding and housing the homeless and veterans of their city. The team from Miriam’s Kitchen shared:

“Miriam’s Kitchen is happy to continue our partnership with Dog Tag Bakery to provide quality baked goods for our meals program. We prepare healthy scratch-made meals for the people experiencing homelessness in D.C. to create a gateway to social services to help achieve our mission to end chronic and veteran homelessness. It starts with a meal; the goal is housing!”
 
Dog Tag Bakery is a non-profit bakery that runs an education and employment program for veterans with disabilities, military spouses, and caregivers. They shared:
 
“Dog Tag is proud to support Miriam’s Kitchen, a local non-profit that provides critical services to the homeless population in our neighborhood and across the District of Columbia. The mission of Miriam’s Kitchen embodies the same spirit of service that drives Dog Tag every day. We are thrilled to partner with Executive Chef Cheryl Bell and our very own Dog Tag Alumnus, Sous Chef Patrick Mason, to help combat chronic homelessness in D.C.”

Together, the bakers of Dog Tag and Miriam’s Kitchen supplied meals and baked goods for the homeless and the Dog Tag Fellowship program which supports veterans. Thank you for your continuous hard work and generosity toward your community!

Learn more about Dog Tag and Miriam’s Kitchen by tapping the link in our profile >> @kingarthurbaking
